{"tid":913213,"cid":19,"subCid":0,"title":"［冇圖］CUHKBanters請你入一入嚟","createTime":"2018-11-23T08:32:07.000Z","updateTime":"2018-11-25T06:50:53.000Z","uid":180233,"like":9,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":9,"replies":[{"pid":"b03857a3370f1611c831bee203ec3b5a9610292f","tid":913213,"uid":180233,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-23T08:32:07.000Z","msg":"好柒<br />\n又長又譖  睇落感覺就好似英文版既共式中文<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/chicken.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/chicken.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n<br />\nAgger <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/like.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />  佢依啲英文叫bombastic，就係用好多好似好難, 好複雜嘅英文詞語同grammar去表現到自己可經好sophisticated，但係佢段文章90%都係廢話. IMO 咁嘅英文鬼老一讀就知你係廢料，扮蟹<br />\n<br />\nBombastic:<br />\n<a href=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/zht/詞典/英語/bombastic\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fdictionary.cambridge.org%2Fzht%2F%E8%A9%9E%E5%85%B8%2F%E8%8B%B1%E8%AA%9E%2Fbombastic&d=1hC2mXRqFVwtGDzsKQdeR54%2BuNhYgvPKbWZYs3KJomg%3D&h=2a4dec62\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://dictionary.cambridge.org/zht/詞典/英語/bombastic</a><br />\n<br />\nusing long and difficult words, <strong>usually to make people think you know more than you do:</strong> <br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/bombastic\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.collinsdictionary.com%2Fdictionary%2Fenglish%2Fbombastic&d=1hC2mXRqFVwtGDzsKQdeR54%2BuNhYgvPKbWZYs3KJomg%3D&h=e6784d10\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/bombastic</a><br />\nIf you describe someone as bombastic, you are criticizing them for trying to impress other people by <strong>saying things that sound impressive but have little meaning. </strong>"},{"pid":"8fdb603388e70858d65712cb7a87311d68a44a2a","tid":913213,"uid":212119,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-23T08:38:32.000Z","msg":"死圖？<img src=\"/assets/faces/